result.notes:
Analysis results of a survey carried out in Jan-Feb 1983 to investigate the 
vertical and horizontal distribution of macroplankton, specifically the 
abundance of early stage (1) plaice eggs, in the Southern Bight area of the 
North Sea. Plankton samples were collected at each site on a planned survey 
grid. This data consists of the numbers of fish eggs and larvae, along with 
associated positional data and volumes filtered.
